query-r01.rq.deftemplate: Implementations shall support the SPARQL Query Language for RDF [W3C SPARQL], the SPARQL Protocol for RDF [W3C SPARQL Protocol] and the SPARQL Query Results XML Format [W3C SPARQL Result Format]

query-r02.rq.deftemplate: Implementations shall allow the RDFS class geo:SpatialObject to be used in SPARQL graph patterns.

query-r03.rq.deftemplate: Implementations shall allow the RDFS class geo:Feature to be used in SPARQL graph patterns.

query-r04.rq.deftemplate: Implementations shall allow the property {{items}} to be used in SPARQL graph patterns.

query-r05.rq.deftemplate: Implementations shall allow the property {{items}} to be used in SPARQL graph patterns.

query-r06.rq.deftemplate: Implementations shall allow the property {{items}} to be used in SPARQL graph patterns.

query-r07.rq.deftemplate: Implementations shall allow the RDFS class geo:Geometry to be used in SPARQL graph patterns.

query-r08.rq.deftemplate: Implementations shall allow the property {{items}} to be used in SPARQL graph patterns.

query-r09.rq.deftemplate: Implementations shall allow the property {{items}} to be used in SPARQL graph patterns.

query-r10.rq.deftemplate: All RDFS Literals of type geo:wktLiteral shall consist of an optional URI identifying the coordinate reference system followed by Simple Features Well Known Text (WKT) describing a geometric value. Valid geo:wktLiterals are formed by concatenating a valid, absolute URI as defined in [RFC 2396], one or more spaces (Unicode U+0020 character) as a separator, and a WKT string as defined in Simple Features [ISO 19125-1].

query-r11.rq.deftemplate: The URI <http://www.opengis.net/def/crs/OGC/1.3/CRS84> shall be assumed as the spatial reference system for geo:wktLiterals that do not specify an explicit spatial reference system URI.

query-r12.rq.deftemplate: Coordinate tuples within geo:wktLiterals shall be interpreted using the axis order defined in the spatial reference system used.

query-r13.rq.deftemplate: An empty RDFS Literal of type geo:wktLiteral shall be interpreted as an empty geometry. Part {{index}} tests {{items}} geometries.

query-r14.rq.deftemplate: Implementations shall allow the RDF property geo:asWKT to be used in SPARQL graph patterns.

query-r15.rq.deftemplate: All geo:gmlLiterals shall consist of a valid element from the GML schema that implements a subtype of GM_Object as defined in [OGC 07-036].

query-r16.rq.deftemplate: An empty geo:gmlLiteral shall be interpreted as an empty geometry. Part {{index}} tests {{items}} geometries.

query-r18.rq.deftemplate: Implementations shall allow the RDF property geo:asGML to be used in SPARQL graph patterns.

query-r19.rq.deftemplate: Implementations shall support {{items}} as a SPARQL extension function, consistent with the definition of the corresponding function distance in Simple Features [ISO 19125-1].

query-r20.rq.deftemplate: Implementations shall support {{items}} as a SPARQL extension function.

query-r21.rq.deftemplate: Implementations shall support {{items}} as a SPARQL extension function, consistent with the relate operator defined in Simple Features [ISO 19125-1].

query-r22.rq.deftemplate: Implementations shall support {{items}} as a SPARQL extension function, consistent with its corresponding DE-9IM intersection pattern, as defined by Simple Features [ISO 19125-1].

query-r23.rq.deftemplate: Implementations shall support {{items}} as a SPARQL extension function, consistent with its corresponding DE-9IM intersection pattern, as defined by Simple Features [ISO 19125-1].

query-r24.rq.deftemplate: Implementations shall support {{items}} as a SPARQL extension function, consistent with its corresponding DE-9IM intersection pattern, as defined by Simple Features [ISO 19125-1].

query-r25.rq.deftemplate: Basic graph pattern matching shall use the semantics defined by the RDFS Entailment Regime [W3C SPARQL Entailment]. Part {{index}} tests {{items}}.

query-r27.rq.deftemplate: Implementations shall support graph patterns involving terms from an RDFS/OWL class hierarchy of geometry types consistent with the GML schema that implements GM_Object using the specified version of GML [OGC 07-036].

query-r28.rq.deftemplate: Basic graph pattern matching shall use the semantics defined by the RIF Core Entailment Regime [W3C SPARQL Entailment] for the RIF rule [W3C RIF Core] {{items}}.

reqToDescs.query-r10.rq: All RDFS Literals of type geo:wktLiteral shall consist of an optional URI identifying the coordinate reference system followed by Simple Features Well Known Text (WKT) describing a geometric value. Valid geo:wktLiterals are formed by concatenating a valid, absolute URI as defined in [RFC 2396], one or more spaces (Unicode U+0020 character) as a separator, and a WKT string as defined in Simple Features [ISO 19125-1].
reqToDescs.query-r11.rq: The URI <http://www.opengis.net/def/crs/OGC/1.3/CRS84> shall be assumed as the spatial reference system for geo:wktLiterals that do not specify an explicit spatial reference system URI.
reqToDescs.query-r12.rq: Coordinate tuples within geo:wktLiterals shall be interpreted using the axis order defined in the spatial reference system used.
reqToDescs.query-r13-1.rq: An empty RDFS Literal of type geo:wktLiteral shall be interpreted as an empty geometry. Part 1 tests LineString geometries.
reqToDescs.query-r13-2.rq: An empty RDFS Literal of type geo:wktLiteral shall be interpreted as an empty geometry. Part 2 tests Point geometries.
reqToDescs.query-r14.rq: Implementations shall allow the RDF property geo:asWKT to be used in SPARQL graph patterns.
reqToDescs.query-r15.rq: All geo:gmlLiterals shall consist of a valid element from the GML schema that implements a subtype of GM_Object as defined in [OGC 07-036].
reqToDescs.query-r16-1.rq: An empty geo:gmlLiteral shall be interpreted as an empty geometry. Part 1 tests LineString geometries.
reqToDescs.query-r16-2.rq: An empty geo:gmlLiteral shall be interpreted as an empty geometry. Part 2 tests Point geometries.
reqToDescs.query-r18.rq: Implementations shall allow the RDF property geo:asGML to be used in SPARQL graph patterns.
